	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Perhaps you haven't experimented enough.  As far as mana efficiency, AE are more efficient than DDs if you think about it.  If you add up the dmg one cast of a AE does to all the mobs, it turns out to be at least twice than the same level DDs do in one cast.  The only problem is the arggo control.  If you know what you are doing, this isn't a problem either.<BR>
Your info on root is wrong.  You are talking about enstill.  Root doesn't break when you cast on a mobs.  It is strictly time based.  Enstill's chances of breaking increases with every hit.  You shouldn't be using root/enstill for AEs anyway.  Get an enchanter to chain stun while you AE.  Use AE for 4 or less mobs, and PBs for more.<BR>
<BR>
Clemidane, 50th Wiz, Veeshan
				</font>
			</td>

